com.davidbracewell.collection.list

Interface Lists


  • public interface Lists

    Convenience methods for creating lists and manipulating collections resulting in lists.

    Author:
    David B. Bracewell

                               Collection<? extends I> collection,
                               @NonNull
                               SerializableFunction<? super I,? extends O> transform)

        Transforms a given collection using a supplied transform function returning the results as a list.

        Type Parameters:
        I - the component type of the collection being transformed
        O - the component type of the resulting collection after transformation
        Parameters:
        collection - the collection to be transformed
        transform - the function used to transform elements of type E to R
        Returns:
        A list containing the transformed items of the supplied collection

      • filter

        static <E> List<E> filter(@NonNull
                          Collection<? extends E> collection,
                          @NonNull
                          SerializablePredicate<? super E> filter)

        Filters a given collection using a supplied predicate returning the results as a list.

        Type Parameters:
        E - the component type of the collection being filtered
        Parameters:
        collection - the collection to be filtered
        filter - the predicate to use for filtering (only items that result in true will be keep)
        Returns:
        A list containing the filtered items of the supplied collection

      • ensureSize

        static <T> List<T> ensureSize(@NonNull
                              List<T> list,
                              int desiredSize,
                              T defaultValue)

        Ensures that the size of the given list is at least the supplied desired size. If the list size is smaller, it will add the given default value to the end of the list until list.size() >= desiredSize

        Type Parameters:
        T - the component type of the list
        Parameters:
        list - the list whose size is being checked
        desiredSize - the desired size of the list
        defaultValue - the default value to add to the list to reach the desired size
        Returns:
        the list passed in with size greater than or equal to the desired size
